<caption> The successive function value is greater than previous value.</caption>
</figure>
</para>
<example id="example-18">

<para id="element-18"><term>Problem : </term> Determine monotonic nature of the function in the interval [0,∞).
</para>
<para id="element-19">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>y</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-20"><term>Solution : </term> Let <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>

 and <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math> belong to the interval [0,∞) such that <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math> &lt; <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>. Multiplying inequality with <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math> (a positive number) does not change the nature of inequality :
</para>
<para id="element-20a">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:msubsup>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msubsup>
    <m:mo>&lt;</m:mo>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>



</para>
<para id="element-20b">
Multiplying inequality with <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math> (a positive number) does not change the nature of inequality :


</para>
<para id="element-20c">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
    <m:msub>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
    <m:mo>&lt;</m:mo>
    <m:msubsup>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msubsup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>




</para>
<para id="element-20d">Combining two inequalities,


</para>
<para id="element-20e">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:msubsup>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msubsup>
    <m:mo>&lt;</m:mo>
    <m:msubsup>
      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msubsup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:mi>f</m:mi>
    <m:mfenced>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:msub>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        </m:msub>
      </m:mrow>
    </m:mfenced>
    <m:mo>&lt;</m:mo>
    <m:mi>f</m:mi>
    <m:mfenced>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:msub>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
